00:16:00.110 --> 00:16:02.150
And it's breaking
down this lactose

00:16:02.150 --> 00:16:05.360
into smaller, simpler
sugars that we can actually

00:16:05.360 --> 00:16:06.740
digest without any problem.

00:16:06.740 --> 00:16:09.350
So this is what this
lovely little calf has.

00:16:09.350 --> 00:16:11.480
And it's what all
baby mammals have.

00:16:11.480 --> 00:16:13.310
But then at a certain
point, what happens

00:16:13.310 --> 00:16:17.990
is the gene switches off,
and the enzyme switches off.

00:16:17.990 --> 00:16:18.728
Very good.

00:16:18.728 --> 00:16:20.270
And so this is what
normally happens.

00:16:20.270 --> 00:16:21.950
