00:16:25.010 --> 00:16:28.130
Lots of you, and including
some adults, as well.

00:16:28.130 --> 00:16:30.140
But that's because,
in many humans,

00:16:30.140 --> 00:16:32.150
there's an adaptation
to dairy culture, which

00:16:32.150 --> 00:16:36.440
means that the gene stays on,
and the enzyme keeps going,

00:16:36.440 --> 00:16:39.890
and you're still able to break
down this lactose sugar well

00:16:39.890 --> 00:16:42.140
into adulthood-- in fact,
for the rest of your life.

00:16:42.140 --> 00:16:44.840
And when we look at what parts
of the world this happened in,

00:16:44.840 --> 00:16:48.020
it happens in parts of the world
where we have dairy culture.

00:16:48.020 --> 00:16:52.130
It happened in dairy cultures
in Africa and in Europe.

